{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644765"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:07:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:07:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18062"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18062"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10776"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105613"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10776"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18062"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88042"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5745"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25130"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25999"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26095"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105613","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/105613"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA general practitioner is considering participating as an investigator in a clinical trial of a new antihypertensive medication. The pharmaceutical company is offering a financial incentive for the GP for each patient successfully enrolled. The practice has a large number of patients with hypertension who may be eligible.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary ethical concern in this scenario?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dual loyalty between patient care and financial interests","Coercion of vulnerable patients into research","Inappropriate influence on prescribing patterns","Compromise of clinical independence","Unfair access to experimental treatments"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary ethical concern is the \u003Cstrong\u003Edual loyalty between patient care and financial interests\u003C/strong\u003E. The substantial per-patient payment creates a conflict between the doctor\u0027s professional obligation to provide unbiased care and their financial interest in trial recruitment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options, while related concerns, are not the primary ethical issue:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoercion of vulnerable patients into research\u003C/strong\u003E is a valid concern, but the primary issue relates to the doctor\u0027s conflict between professional duties and financial gain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInappropriate influence on prescribing patterns\u003C/strong\u003E represents a potential consequence of the conflict of interest rather than the core ethical issue itself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECompromise of clinical independence\u003C/strong\u003E describes an outcome that may result from the conflict of interest rather than the fundamental ethical problem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnfair access to experimental treatments\u003C/strong\u003E is not directly related to the core ethical issue of competing interests in this scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe solution requires careful management of competing interests through mechanisms such as ethical oversight, transparent disclosure, and separation of recruitment decisions from financial incentives.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A conflict of interest occurs when a healthcare provider\u0027s personal interests could compromise their professional judgement or obligations.","Financial relationships with pharmaceutical companies are a common source of conflicts of interest in healthcare.","Disclosure of potential conflicts of interest is an ethical requirement in medical practice and research."],"references":["Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88042"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18062"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88042"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-10T22:43:08+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-10T22:43:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10776"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105613"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74